LAGOS – As part of the drive to enhance the promotion of green energy, while serving customers with quality petroleum products, leading petroleum marketing and distribution company, Fatgbems Petroleum, has unveiled its first Solar Powered Retail Station in Abeokuta, Ogun State Capital. The new retail outlet which is part of the strategic plan of the company to expand its retail presence across Nigeria was designed and implemented by Constructuno Services, a top construction and project company. Mr. Adebayo Gbemisola, Executive Director, Retail Business, while speaking at the event, disclosed that the new marketplace character is one that combines attractive ambiance, quality product offering with top-notch customer experience and services. “As a company, we are always in touch with our customer’s needs which is the bedrock of service offerings” he stressed. Mr. Gbemisola further added that Oke-Sokori is a strategic move to cater to the growing market in Abeokuta with something that is beyond the norms among retail stations around. “The aesthetics of the station and the installation of full capacity solar has a lot to do with our values which is the main connection between the company and the teeming customers” he explained. He also added that the new retail outlet is a full experience hub that will not just cater to petroleum product needs only but will provide a one-stop experience with a fully integrated mart, tyre shop, Carpro auto care center, and a gas retailing shelf. The station is fully in operation for the comfort and convenience of the customers in and around Abeokuta. While another masterpiece station will be commissioned soon in Lagos State. POLL Fatgbems Petroleum Company Limited is a member of Fatgbems Group. A company incorporated as an independent petroleum marketing company and tyre trading company delivering service satisfaction and value to customers.